feat(skcomm): full source + 11 new modules from transport-builder session

Core library (pre-existing, first commit to git):
- transport.py: pluggable Transport ABC with health checks
- models.py: MessageEnvelope, RoutingConfig, MessageType (+ HEARTBEAT)
- router.py: multi-mode routing with failover/broadcast/stealth/speed
- core.py: SKComm engine with send/receive/status
- config.py: YAML config loader, cli.py: Click CLI

Transports:
- transports/syncthing.py: P2P file-based via Syncthing mesh
- transports/file.py: local filesystem message drops
- transports/nostr.py: NIP-17/NIP-44/NIP-59 encrypted DMs over Nostr relays

New modules (transport-builder, 11 tasks):
- discovery.py: peer auto-discovery (Syncthing + file + mDNS)
- heartbeat.py: file-based alive/dead detection
- marketplace.py: SKWorld skill publish/search via Nostr kind 30078
- queue.py: persistent message queue with retry backoff and TTL expiry
- compression.py: gzip/zstd envelope compression
- ack.py: delivery acknowledgment tracker with timeout detection
- metrics.py: per-transport delivery stats and latency tracking
- ratelimit.py: token bucket throttling per transport and per peer

CLI: discover, heartbeat, skill, queue, stats commands
Tests: 386 passing across 18 test files
